So, now let's show how we will determine each of the entries on the Post-merger balance sheet:

- The **Current assets** is the sum of the current assets of the Firms:
$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Current assets}&=\text{Current assets }_{\text{Meat Co}}+\text{Current assets }_{\text{Loaf, Inc.}}\\
&=\$18,000+\$3,900\\
&=\bold{\$21,900}
\end{align*}
$$

- The **Net Fixed Assets** is also the sum of the net fixed assets of the Firms: 
$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Net Fixed Assets}&=\text{Net Fixed Assets }_{\text{Meat Co}}+\text{Net Fixed Assets }_{\text{Loaf, Inc.}}\\
&=\$43,000+\$9,800\\
&=\bold{\$52,800}
\end{align*}
$$

- The **Goodwill** is determined as the amount that Meat Co. pays for Meat Co. less the Net Assets of Loaf Inc.


$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Net assets }_{\text{Loaf, Inc.}}&=\text{Total assets }_{\text{Loaf, Inc.}}-\left(\begin{array}{c}
\text{Long-term}\\
\text{debt}
\end{array}+\begin{array}{c}
\text{Current}\\
\text{liabilities}
\end{array}\right)_{\text{Loaf, Inc.}}\\[10pt]
&=\underbrace{(\$9,800+\$3,900)}_{\text{Fixed assets $+$ Current assets}}-(\$2,600+\$1,500)\\[20pt]
&=\$9,600
\end{align*}
$$
Now, let's use the information provided in table 3 about the purchase value, and let's calculate the **Goodwill** value:
$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Goodwill}&=\$17,800-\$9,600\\
&=\bold{\$8,200}
\end{align*}
$$

- The **current liabilities** is the sum of the current liabilities of the Firms: 
$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Current liabilities}&=\text{Current liabilities }_{\text{Meat Co}}+\text{Current liabilities }_{\text{Loaf, Inc.}}\\
&=\$6,100+\$1,500\\
&=\bold{\$7,600}
\end{align*}
$$

- Now, **long-term debt** is the sum of each company's long-term debt plus the loan requested to acquire Loaf, Inc.

$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Long-term debt}&=\begin{array}{c}
\text{Long-term}\\
\text{debt}
\end{array}_{\text{Meat Co}}+\begin{array}{c}
\text{Long-term}\\
\text{debt}
\end{array}_{\text{Loaf, Inc.}}+\text{Acquisition }_{\text{Loaf, Inc.}}\\
&=\$13,700+\$2,600+\$17,800\\
&=\bold{\$34,100}
\end{align*}
$$

And finally, 
- **Equity** is taken from the acquiring company:

$$\text{Equity}=\text{Equity}_{\text{Meat Co}}=\bold{\$41,200}$$

Now we are ready to create the Post-merger balance sheet, are you ready? Let's do it!

In the following table, we show the post-merger balance sheet according to the purchase method of accounting. 

$$
\begin{array}{c}
\textbf{Post-merger balance sheet according to}\\ 
\textbf{the purchase method of accounting}
\end{array}
$$


$$
\begin{array}{l c| l c}
\hline
\text{Current assets}&\$\hspace{5pt}21,900 &\text{Current liabilities} &\$\hspace{10pt}7,600 \\
\text{Net fixed assets} &\hspace{10pt}52,800 &\text{Long-term debt} & \hspace{10pt}34,100\\
&&\text{Equity}&\hspace{10pt}41,200\\
\text{Goodwill} &\hspace{15pt}8,200\\
\textbf{Total} &\overline{\underline{\underline{\$\hspace{5pt}82,900}}} &\textbf{Total} &\overline{\underline{\underline{\$\hspace{5pt}82,900}}}
\end{array}
$$
